The Generative Models use machine learning and deep learning to learn a distribution from training data and then generate new examples from the distribution. The general form can be represented as: \[
p(\mathrm{x} | \mathrm{c}, \mathrm{w})
\] where the \(\mathrm{c}\) represents a vector of conditioning variables, for example, a class label(cat, dog,…), a sentence, and the \(\mathrm{w}\) represent the learnable parameters of the models.
However, for real world application, the distribution is extremely complex so that we need deep neural network to improved the performance of generative models. There are several important deep generative models:
